#edit?e&w&p=TASK: output HTML wireframe for a file editor
  - fields: textarea
  - components: status bar with character count
  - just HTML and CSS
  - use flex to make the textarea fill full height of window
  - no javascript
  - dont include html/head/body tags just the wireframe
&w&a=1&p=TASK: output a SCRIPT tag that adds autosaving
  - `read()`, `write()`, and `name` are globally available to you
  - use `read(name).then(callback)` to read the current page into the textarea
  - on textarea update autosave the contents with `write(value, name).then(callback)`
  - run immediately, do not wait for DOMContentLoaded etc
  - listen for URL hash fragment changes
    - `name` will automatically contain the new file name
    - update the textarea with the new page content
  - focus the textarea
&w&a=1&p=TASK: output a SCRIPT tag that adds statusbar features
  - on textarea input update the statusbar to show number of characters and bytes in the editor
&w&a=1&p=TASK: output a SCRIPT tag that reloads the editor when edited from another browser tab
  - use broadcast channel api to trigger an event when the editor changes, passing the global filename in `name`
  - listen to this same broadcast, if the current `name` matches the one in the event, use `read(name).then(callback)` to load in the data
  - don't dispatch event if called from same browser tab
&w

